{
  "style": "APA",
  "texts": [
    "Gambling is a significant and growing form of entertainment, participated in by millions globally.",
    "While most consumers enjoy gambling as a leisure activity, a small percentage of participants experience serious harms, while a larger proportion may experience some subclinical negative effects (Tran et al., 2024).",
    "The industry's rapid expansion, driven largely by digitization and the global availability of online and mobile products, has led to a corresponding increase in efforts to mitigate these potential harms (Ghaharian et al., 2022).",
    "These collective efforts are commonly referred to as Responsible Gambling (RG) foot_0.",
    "RG strategies have evolved as a direct result of gambling's digitization, and include targeted RG messaging, immediate access to gambling help resources, and automated risk detection systems (Shaffer et al., 2020)."
  ],
  "correct_citations": [
    "While most consumers enjoy gambling as a leisure activity, a small percentage of participants experience serious harms, while a larger proportion may experience some subclinical negative effects (Tran et al., 2024).",
    "The industry's rapid expansion, driven largely by digitization and the global availability of online and mobile products, has led to a corresponding increase in efforts to mitigate these potential harms (Ghaharian et al., 2022).",
    "RG strategies have evolved as a direct result of gambling's digitization, and include targeted RG messaging, immediate access to gambling help resources, and automated risk detection systems (Shaffer et al., 2020)."
  ]
}